# Service Rules

Services contain **all business logic**. They must not know Express `Request`/`Response`.

## Responsibilities

- Orchestrate Prisma queries and `$transaction`
- Hash/verify passwords (Argon2), issue/revoke tokens
- Enforce ownership and RBAC rules (IDOR prevention)
- Write `auditLog` entries for security-sensitive actions
- Throw `AppError(status, message, code, details?)`

## Must not

- Call `res.json()` or read HTTP headers directly (pass meta from controller)
- Skip authorization checks for user-scoped resources
- Return different shapes for the same operation across endpoints

## Pattern

```typescript
async updateUser(actorId: string, targetId: string, data: UpdateInput, meta: RequestMeta) {
  if (actorId !== targetId && !await this.isAdmin(actorId)) {
    throw new AppError(403, "Forbidden", "FORBIDDEN");
  }
  return prisma.user.update({ where: { id: targetId }, data });
}
```

Keep services focused per module (`auth.service.ts`, not a god service).
